          <fn id="ece38649-note-0005">
            <p>−NRI cannot be calculated for taxa that associate with a single partner. Therefore, we were not able to calculate −NRI for 100% of taxa in some datasets. Values before backslash are percentage of taxa, and values after backslash are percentage of interaction frequencies. Totals within a species set and index may not sum to 100 due to rounding. All calculations were based on interaction frequencies as a proxy for availability. See Figure <xref rid="ece38649-fig-0005" ref-type="fig">5</xref> for a comparison of PSS values based on direct empirical estimations of availability versus interaction frequencies as a proxy for availability.</p>
