          <p>Comparison of PSS values estimated using empirical estimates of availability (empirical avail.) obtained from surveys of species abundances (X axis) vs using the marginal sum of interaction frequencies (interact. freq.) obtained from an interaction matrix as a proxy for availability (Y axis). PSS of (a) mammal partners of flea species, (b) plants in the hummingbird pollination dataset, and (c) the hummingbirds. Each circle on these plots represents a species. The thresholds for the shaded areas (random phylogenetic structure) were defined as the mean of the 95% confidence interval of the null distributions generated for each taxon in the datasets. Points on the diagonal red line indicate identical PSS values</p>
        </caption>
